# Fixerrors Workflow

- Run `npm run fixerrors` for the normal analyze-and-clear workflow.
- Use `npm run fixerrors -- --no-clear` when reviewing or validating without deleting remote error rows.
- Read `docs_private/error-analysis.md` after a successful run.
- Read `docs_private/error-fix-log.md` when it exists, plus generated automation review/follow-up files.
- Summarize actionable error groups without reproducing sensitive payloads, tokens, user data, or full stack traces.
- Claim remote errors were cleared only when the automation run log explicitly records a successful clear step.
- Keep every generated error and automation artifact local and ignored.

